ðŸ“˜ Product Requirements Document (PRD)
Product Name: Kulmis Academy
1. Product Overview

Kulmis Academy is a modern, AI-enhanced Learning Management System (LMS) designed for individual ownership (single admin model). The platform delivers high-quality technology and AI-focused courses to students globally, with a Free and Pro subscription model.

The system will be built using:

Next.js (Fullstack framework)

Tailwind CSS (Neon UI design system)

Sanity (Headless CMS for course content)

PostgreSQL (User & subscription data)

Stripe (Subscription payments)

Clerk (Authentication)

Hosted on Vercel

The platform will prioritize:

Clean architecture

High performance

Modern neon UI aesthetic

Scalable SaaS-ready structure

2. Product Vision

To build a visually stunning, high-performance digital learning platform that empowers Somali and global learners to master technology, AI, and modern development skills.

Kulmis Academy should feel:

Futuristic

Professional

Minimal

Neon-accented

Fast and smooth

3. Target Users
Primary Users

Students interested in:

Web Development

AI & Machine Learning

Vibe Coding

Software Engineering

Admin

Single platform owner

Full control over courses and revenue

No instructor accounts

4. Core Features
4.1 Authentication System

Using Clerk:

Email/password signup

Google OAuth login

Secure sessions

Role-based access:

Admin

Student

4.2 Subscription Model
Free Plan

Limited course access

No certificate downloads

No premium resources

Basic dashboard access

Pro Plan

Full course access

Downloadable resources

Certificates

Priority updates

Future premium features

Stripe Integration:

Monthly subscription

Annual subscription

Webhook handling

Auto renewal

Cancel anytime

4.3 Course Management (Admin Only)

Managed via Sanity CMS.

Admin can:

Create course

Edit course

Delete course

Add lessons

Upload video links

Upload resources (PDF, ZIP)

Set course visibility (Free/Pro)

Course Schema:

Course:

Title

Slug

Description

Thumbnail

Category

Level

Price (if needed)

Access type (Free or Pro)

Lessons (array)

Lesson:

Title

Video URL

Description

Resources

Order number

4.4 Student Dashboard

Features:

Enrolled courses

Continue watching

Progress tracking

Subscription status

Upgrade to Pro button

Profile settings

4.5 Progress Tracking

Stored in PostgreSQL:

user_id

course_id

lesson_id

completion_status

last_watched_timestamp

Features:

Auto-save progress

Resume where you left off

Course completion percentage

4.6 Admin Dashboard

Admin-only protected route.

Features:

Total users

Active Pro subscriptions

Revenue summary

Course list

Create/edit/delete courses

View subscription analytics

